in aone-time undisclosed restructuring charge for the fiscal quarter ending Feb.andO;28.andP;  National reported a net loss of $55.7 million for the first half of itsfiscal year that ended Nov.andP;  27.andM;Analysts, noting that National's semiconductor chips sales were up by 14percent last year, compared with an industry average of 37 percent, said thelayoffs were expected.andP;  Company President Charles Sporck said the layoffs arepart of a reorganization that will help the company focus on its coresemiconductor business.andM;Intel Profit Sets RecordandM;Calling it a year that ''started strong and ended weak,'' Intel Corp. lastweek reported record revenue and profit for 1988.andP;  Revenue for the fiscalyear ended Dec.andP;  31, 1988, was $2.9 billion, up 51 percent from 1987.andP;  Profitfor the Santa Clara, Calif., company was $453 million, or $2.51 per share, up83 percent from one year ago.andM;Profit for the quarter ended Dec.andP;  31, however, slipped from $96 million, or55 cents per share, one year ago, to $86 million, or 46 cents per share.andM;Large inventories of Intel's 80386 chips are considered to be the biggestfactor in Intel's fourth-quarter fall.andO;</TEXT></DOC>